reviews.review:
This movie has everything. Heart, drama, beauty and fun. It's an excellent heartfelt adventure with brilliant vocal performances and a lovely moral code. Pixar really confirm their place as the best animation studio in the business.
The only areas in which this movie suffers is that sometimes it's hard to forget how unnecessary it was considering the perfect ending of Toy Story 3.
However, that is a minor issue. This film is excellent and is definitely the best family movie of the year so far. If you haven't seen it already, be sure to check it out.
I wouldn't have believed you until I saw it myself. They once again deliver an excellent story with great stakes and a little something that comes out of nowhere.
A fresh look at our friend's story which we thought is not possible. Just Great!

Pixar has spent 20 years telling us the most important thing in the world for a toy is not to abandon their kid. And I cried and I bought it. Then they end the 4 movies with Woody abandoning his kid and his friends to live in a dirty park. I guess the first 3 movies were just BS then...
There's only so much more toy related antics that can be new, but the fun atmosphere of Toy Story is still here

It brought a tear to my eye as did the previous one . For a cartoon it has so much emotion in it . Very funny with a meaningful and well constructed story.  Sadly it appears to be the final chapter to the "Toy Story" line. Unbelievably great movies! I was a bit dissapointed the original main characters play a minimal role in the plot along with minimal screen time as well. Buzz Lightyear is practically a minor character since his role lacks significance  to the plot tremendously if you compare it to the previous "toy story's" and they also make his personality appear dimwitted pretty often which just simply looks not right if you've watched 1 ,2 and 3. Even less importance are Jessie, Bullseye, Slinky,Potato Heads, Rex etc .. shaved a half star for that. Still excellent but it ranks the lowest in the saga to me.  I understand if you don't like the bittersweet ending. Some say the 3rd is how it should have ended which ends on a more positive note. Still i give it 9/10.
